.TH "i2c_transfer" 9 "i2c_transfer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i2c_transfer \- execute a single or combined I2C message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i2c_transfer
.BI "(struct i2c_adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "struct i2c_msg *msgs "  ","
.BI "int num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
Handle to I2C bus
.IP "msgs" 12
One or more messages to execute before STOP is issued to
terminate the operation; each message begins with a START.
.IP "num" 12
Number of messages to be executed.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns negative errno, else the number of messages executed.

Note that there is no requirement that each message be sent to
the same slave address, although that is the most common model.
